org.knime.core.data.append

Class AppendedRowsRowInput

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.knime.core.node.streamable.PortInput
      • org.knime.core.node.streamable.RowInput
        • org.knime.core.data.append.AppendedRowsRowInput

  • public class AppendedRowsRowInput
extends RowInput
    Extended RowInput that pulls its data from an array of argument RowInput. For duplicate Row-ID handling, column mis-matches etc. see AppendedRowsTable for details.
    Since:
    3.1
    Author:
    Bernd Wiswedel, KNIME.com, Zurich, Switzerland

      • poll

        public DataRow poll()
             throws InterruptedException
        Get the next row from the input stream. The call may block if upstream nodes are still in the process of generating data. Client code could look like this: 
         DataRow row;
 while ((row = rowInput.poll()) != null) {
     // do something with row
 }
 rowInput.close();
        Specified by:
        poll in class RowInput
        Returns:
        The next row or null if the end of the stream has been reached.
        Throws:
        InterruptedException - If canceled.

      • create

        public static AppendedRowsRowInput create(RowInput[] ins,
                                          AppendedRowsTable.DuplicatePolicy duplPolicy,
                                          String suffix,
                                          ExecutionMonitor exec,
                                          long totalRowCount)
        Concatenates a set of Inputs. Duplicates are handled according to the policy argument. Columns present in one input but not the others or conflicting column tables are handled as described in AppendedRowsTable.
        Parameters:
        ins - all inputs to be appended (non-null and no null values allowed)
        duplPolicy - How to deal with duplicate keys. Non-null.
        suffix - suffix to append to duplicate keys (must not be null if policy is AppendedRowsTable.DuplicatePolicy.AppendSuffix)
        exec - (optional) execution monitor that is used to report progress and check for cancelation. Can be null.
        totalRowCount - The number of rows to expect (sum over all row counts in the inputs). Only be used for progress -- can be negative to have no progress.
        Returns:
        a new row input whose iteration scans all argument inputs.
